Following controversies trailing the election of the presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State, a frontline presidential aspirant in the party has vowed never to be cowed into stepping down for any candidate, stressing that he will only step down on the order of President Muhammadu Buhari. The governor said that he does not belong to a minority group, but a popular generation and maintained that he would resist any attempt by any group in whatever guise to use intimidation to ask him to step down. Yahaya Bello who spoke on Arise Television on Tuesday said that he has a lot of respect for the President and that he (Buhari) is the only one who can ask him to step down and he would listen. He said, “I will not step down for anybody. Only President Muhammadu Buhari can ask me to step down. I don’t belong to a minority group, I belong to a generation of people who are in the majority and so I will not allow anybody or group of people to use intimidation to cow me into stepping down for anybody. “I will resist any attempt by any group of people in whatever guise to talk me into stepping down.  I respect the President, if he asks me to step down, I will step down.”